        "prompt": "Design an original, non-infringing infographic poster in the style of a Chinese national museum exhibition panel, presenting a detailed visual guide to a traditional Miao ethnic minority costume.\n\nStyle/medium: museum exhibition infographic, archival illustration style with technical diagram precision, matte paper texture, restrained academic aesthetic inspired by National Museum of China display panels\nComposition: vertical poster layout with structured grid, central full-figure standing subject wearing complete costume, surrounding annotation zones with leader lines pointing to specific components\nSubject: Miao (Hmong) ethnic minority woman's ceremonial festival attire, featuring elaborate silver headdress, embroidered collar jacket, pleated indigo skirt, silver jewelry ornaments, and layered textile construction\nScene/backdrop: warm off-white archival paper background (ivory/rice paper tone), subtle aged texture, clean museum display aesthetic with generous white space\nLighting/mood: even diffused museum lighting, neutral and scholarly atmosphere, no dramatic shadows or highlights\nColor palette: muted archival tones with indigo blue as anchor, silver metallic accents, earthy browns and blacks from natural dyes, restrained and scholarly\nMaterials/textures: hand-woven hemp and cotton base fabrics, wax-resist dyed indigo cloth, intricate silk embroidery with geometric patterns, hand-hammered silver ornaments with repoussé work, detailed close-up swatches showing weave structure\nText (verbatim): \"中国少数民族服饰 · 苗族盛装图鉴\" (main title), \"银饰 · 蜡染 · 刺绣\" (subtitle), component labels: \"银角头饰\", \"刺绣上衣\", \"蜡染百褶裙\", \"银项圈\", \"绑腿\", \"绣花鞋\"\nConstraints: all text must be simplified Chinese characters only, no English or pinyin, text must be legible and properly arranged, layout must follow specified zones (top title, left structural breakdown, upper-right material samples, middle-right pattern/color meanings, bottom wearing sequence), museum-grade 