        "prompt": "Create an original, non-infringing travel guide brochure for a 4-day 3-night Hangzhou trip, featuring a real Hangzhou map as the main visual thread.\n\nStyle/medium: photorealistic editorial brochure design, trifold leaflet mockup floating above textured kraft paper, realistic map cartography with illustrated landmark icons\nComposition: top-down flat lay of a trifold brochure, slightly angled 3/4 view showing all three panels, shallow depth of field with kraft paper base visible at edges\nSubject: trifold travel guide brochure with authentic Hangzhou map as background, famous scenic spots marked with distinctive landmark icons (断桥残雪, 雷峰塔, 灵隐寺, 龙井村, etc.), each day's itinerary highlighted in separate panels\nScene/backdrop: textured kraft paper surface beneath the floating brochure, soft shadow beneath the leaflet suggesting elevation, clean minimal background\nLighting/mood: soft diffused studio lighting from upper left, gentle shadows, professional product photography aesthetic\nColor palette: muted kraft brown as base, Hangzhou map in soft greens and blues, landmark icons in warm terracotta and gold accents, clean white text panels\nMaterials/textures: matte paper texture on brochure, slight sheen on printed map areas, visible fiber texture on kraft paper base, crisp printed typography\nText (verbatim): \"第一天：西湖经典游\" \"断桥残雪→白堤→孤山→曲院风荷→苏堤春晓→花港观鱼→雷峰塔→柳浪闻莺\" \"第二天：禅意杭州\" \"灵隐寺→飞来峰造像→法喜寺→宋城\" \"第三天：九溪烟树徒步\" \"九溪十八涧→龙井村→十里琅珰→云栖竹径\" \"第四天：运河文艺线/西溪湿地\"\nConstraints: must show all three folded panels clearly; map must be geographically accurate to Hangzhou; landmark icons must be recognizable; text must be legible at brochure scale\nAvoid: generic stock travel imagery; blurry map details; plastic-looking paper; watermark; 8K stuffer text; oversaturated colors",
